\section*{Healing by first intentions (Primary union)}

Condition - minimum loss of tissue e.g. In surgical incision healing takes a very short period of time.

\section*{Stages}
1) Exudation of blood into the space between the cut but closely opposite tissues.
2) Coagulation of fluid with formation of fibrin strands.
3) Invasion of this coagulation by capillary loops and fibroblasts derived from marginal tissues.
4) Maturation of fibroblasts whose fibrils lay down collagen which mature and decrease in vascularity to result in to avascular scar tissue.
5) Proliferation of the marginal surface epithelial cells to restore the surface continuity (in 7 days continuity is restored.)

